\ see-compiled shows the compiled body, with fused superwords and their
\ variable operands resolved by name.

variable A  3.0 to A
variable B  4.0 to B

\ two-var, unary-fn, and two-var-mul fusions
: fused  A B f-  A fsq  A B f* ;
' fused see-compiled

\ a literal, a stack+var fusion, and a unary function
: mixed  5.0 A f-  B sqrt ;
' mixed see-compiled

\ a call to another colon word shows that word's name
: calls  A fsq  fused ;
' calls see-compiled

\ see-compiled on a non-colon word reports it
' A see-compiled

\ local-operand arithmetic fusion: <local> <local> op
: ll-arith | a b | a b f+  a b f-  a b f* ;
' ll-arith see-compiled

\ local-literal arithmetic fusion: <local> <literal> op
: lit-arith | a | a 2.0 f+  a 2.0 f-  a 2.0 f* ;
' lit-arith see-compiled

\ literal-local: commutative <lit> <local> reuse (+, *) and reversed subtract
: rev-arith | a | 2.0 a f+  2.0 a f*  2.0 a f- ;
' rev-arith see-compiled

\ @i index fusion: local index, literal index, and local-array + literal index
: at-local-idx | i | [ 10 20 30 ] i @i ;
' at-local-idx see-compiled
: at-lit-idx  [ 10 20 30 ] 1 @i ;
' at-lit-idx see-compiled
: at-lit-of-local | arr | arr 1 @i ;
' at-lit-of-local see-compiled

\ fusion fires inside a quotation on its own (depth-0) locals
[: | >a >b | a b f* :] see-compiled
